Posts.Content: Aug 18, 2010 11:58AM wam12 wrote: If you're worried, you should have it checked out some more.  Doctors can be wrong.  I am 33, have no family history of breast cancer.  I have a lump under my arm and am going for a mammogram, ultrasound and mri.  My doctor thinks my lump is probably not cancerous but wants to make sure and is being extra cautious -- so I don't think you are wrong to get it checked with another test like an ultrasound and/or mri.
